This paper deals with optimizing content delivery and caching placement in wireless networks, which is a problem that falls under the domain of network optimization and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of dynamic programming and Markov decision processes, which are techniques commonly used in information theory and optimization, suggesting that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also likely categories. The paper also deals with optimization and control, which are topics that fall under the domain of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
